    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"479359\">Michael Stoll</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Naming.20convention.3A.20succ.20vs.2E.20add_one/near/537128666\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Should we add that to the technical debt counters? <span aria-label=\"slight smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f642\" role=\"img\" title=\"slight smile\">:slight_smile:</span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>If you find a programmatic way to count these (e.g. <code>grep something something</code>), that's easy to add!</p>",
        "id": 537130373,
        "sender_full_name": "Michael Rothgang",
        "timestamp": 1756739698
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We could probably write an easy regex that would catch most declaration names that contain <code>succ</code>.</p>",
        "id": 537132015,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1756740323
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"873547\">Robin Arnez</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Naming.20convention.3A.20succ.20vs.2E.20add_one/near/537128938\">schrieb</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Is there some way to loogle <code>x and not b</code>?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Not yet (<a href=\"https://github.com/nomeata/loogle/issues/6\">https://github.com/nomeata/loogle/issues/6</a>)</p>",
        "id": 537132183,
        "sender_full_name": "Joachim Breitner",
        "timestamp": 1756740393
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"634338\">Michael Rothgang</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Naming.20convention.3A.20succ.20vs.2E.20add_one/near/537130373\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>If you find a programmatic way to count these (e.g. <code>grep something something</code>), that's easy to add!</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This doesn't seem to be that easy -- the type of the declaration can extend over several lines, and we should check whether it contains <code>succ</code>.</p>",
        "id": 537132409,
        "sender_full_name": "Michael Stoll",
        "timestamp": 1756740479
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Not the type signature, the declaration id.</p>",
        "id": 537132530,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1756740531
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If the id contains <code>succ</code>, it either means that the signature contains <code>succ</code> and should be changed, or the signature already does not contain succ and the name should still be changed!  <span aria-label=\"slight smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f642\" role=\"img\" title=\"slight smile\">:slight_smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 537132617,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1756740568
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But you certainly want to avoid false positives? Like <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Order.succ_mono#doc\">docs#Order.succ_mono</a> etc.</p>",
        "id": 537132722,
        "sender_full_name": "Michael Stoll",
        "timestamp": 1756740605
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah, sorry, I was confused by Michael quoting Michael... <span aria-label=\"man facepalming\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f926-200d-2642\" role=\"img\" title=\"man facepalming\">:man_facepalming:</span></p>",
        "id": 537132747,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1756740613
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"479359\">Michael Stoll</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Naming.20convention.3A.20succ.20vs.2E.20add_one/near/537132722\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>But you certainly want to avoid false positives? Like <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Order.succ_mono#doc\">docs#Order.succ_mono</a> etc.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Well, what I am thinking is that there are probably not that many false positives...</p>",
        "id": 537132838,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1756740648
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"644391\">@loogle</span> Order.succ, \"succ\"</p>",
        "id": 537132917,
        "sender_full_name": "Michael Stoll",
        "timestamp": 1756740676
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"search\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f50d\" role=\"img\" title=\"search\">:search:</span> <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Order/SuccPred/Basic.html#Order.succ\">Order.succ</a>, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Order/SuccPred/Basic.html#Order.succ_mono\">Order.succ_mono</a>, and <a href=\"https://loogle.lean-lang.org/?q=Order.succ%2C%20%22succ%22\">450 more</a></p>",
        "id": 537132919,
        "sender_full_name": "loogle",
        "timestamp": 1756740677
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Otherwise, it would have to be a metaprogram: since this is meant to run on master, where the oleans are available, it is probably pretty quick to run.</p>",
