    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"321459\">Damiano Testa</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Naming.20convention.3A.20succ.20vs.2E.20add_one/near/537145458\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>My impression is that <code>succ</code> is \"more popular\" for historical reasons.  For instance, up until recently, <code>induction n</code> would show a goal involving <code>Nat.succ</code>.  I was certainly happy to see this change.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Do you mean that the lemmas used to talk about <code>Nat.succ</code>, and then the type was changed without changing the name?</p>",
        "id": 537146775,
        "sender_full_name": "Jovan Gerbscheid",
        "timestamp": 1756746394
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>No, this is what I meant:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">induction</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- goal used to be Nat.succ n = Nat.succ n</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 537148268,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1756747120
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So, people were used to have to battle with <code>Nat.succ</code> to convert it to <code>_ + 1</code> and that trickled into having lemmas that involved <code>Nat.succ</code>.</p>",
        "id": 537148329,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1756747155
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I hope that the name was changed, but maybe this has not happened, I am not sure.</p>",
        "id": 537148369,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1756747179
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I am talking about lemmas that have <code>succ</code> in the name, which refers to a <code>_ + 1</code> in the theorem statement. But you are talking about theorems that contain <code>Nat.succ</code>.</p>",
        "id": 537148563,
        "sender_full_name": "Jovan Gerbscheid",
        "timestamp": 1756747288
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(That's why I asked if the types had changed without the names having been changed)</p>",
        "id": 537149488,
        "sender_full_name": "Jovan Gerbscheid",
        "timestamp": 1756747782
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think that there was a period where <code>Nat.succ</code> was so frequent, that <code>Nat.succ</code> and <code>add_one</code> weren't often distinguished very clearly.  I hope that in the cases where the type changed to use <code>_ + 1</code>, the name was also changed to use <code>add_one</code>, but I am not sure if this actually happened consistently or not.</p>",
        "id": 537149952,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1756747970
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, my impression is the same as <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"321459\">@Damiano Testa</span>'s. I did my fair share of naming Nat lemmas that referred to <code>_ + 1</code> with \"<code>succ</code>\" because of this. I remember it feeling unclear on whether <code>succ</code> or <code>add_one</code> should be preferred.</p>",
        "id": 537151217,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1756748618
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In any case, historical reasons aside, even if the decision is not to systematically change all <code>succ</code>s to <code>add_one</code> (names <em>and</em> types), I would still prefer if this was the drift.</p>",
        "id": 537151420,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1756748725
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So, reporting the number produced by the script above in the <del>PR summary</del>tech debt seems like a good idea: it is a small nudge in the right direction, without being an obligation.</p>",
        "id": 537151532,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1756748788
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(In terms of practical matters, this means that the tech debt script will require a Lean component and so the change to CI is not just the addition of a couple of lines.)</p>",
        "id": 537151655,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1756748860
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"246273\">Bhavik Mehta</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Naming.20convention.3A.20succ.20vs.2E.20add_one/near/537143012\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I disagree, since <code>succ</code> could (and in my view, exclusively should) refer to <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Order.succ#doc\">docs#Order.succ</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>And really, in the case of a <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=SuccAddOrder#doc\">docs#SuccAddOrder</a>, we should similarly be using <code>x + 1</code> instead of <code>succ x</code>. That's a long-standing TODO blocked only by <code>Ordinal</code> which annoyingly chose the opposite convention.</p>",
        "id": 537172551,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1756761305
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm very much in favour of changing both names and statements to avoiding mentioning <code>succ</code> where possible.</p>",
        "id": 537179763,
        "sender_full_name": "Kim Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1756766850
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"hot pepper\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f336\" role=\"img\" title=\"hot pepper\">:hot_pepper:</span>: let's rename <code>Nat.succ</code> itself...?</p>",
        "id": 537179804,
